
[1]microscopical

   MICROSCOP'ICAL, a. Made by the aid of a microscope; as microscopic
   observation.

   1. Assisted by a microscope.

   Evading even the microscopic eye.

   2. Resembling a microscope; capable of seeing small objects.

   Why has not man a microscopic eye?

   3. Very small; visible only by the aid of a microscope; as a
   microscopic insect.
